post_text:
Our Athlos families have been finding creative ways to stay busy during the school closure. They go for walks, learn music, and work on distance learning science projects at home! Thank you for sharing Arjay lee!

@Jeni A Dee and her sons learned to sew and made 50 masks for the local care center! Excellent work students!

What activities have your family been up to this week? Share with us in the comments or shoot us a message.

